duction/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052633/P0005744.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/p0005744/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052633/P0005744-1200x743.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eAt the same time, the M3 was also launched in the USA, and given this market being one of their largest, the plan was to embark on racing in the States, too. However, the American GT and Le Mans series were fiercely competitive, and the M3’s straight-six S54 motor was thought to be less formidable compared to those rivals from the likes of Porsche, Chevrolet and more.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054429/DSC01044.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054429/DSC01044-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"DSC01044\" data-attachment-id=\"656899\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054429/DSC01044.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/dsc01044-2/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054429/DSC01044-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe solution? Whip it out in favour of a super compact, super lightweight V8 instead. The problem? This would classify it as a prototype rather than a production car because the P60B40 V8 engine wasn’t available in any E46 M3 at the time. So, to meet homologation needs, a small series of street-legal M3 GTRs were produced (albeit with a slightly detuned version of the P60B40).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054453/DSC01022.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054453/DSC01022-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"DSC01022\" data-attachment-id=\"656904\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054453/DSC01022.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/dsc01022-2/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054453/DSC01022-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eFun fact: This engine has\u003cem\u003e only\u003c/em\u003e ever been in the BMW M3 GTR street version; it’s never appeared in anything else since.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054444/DSC01033.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054444/DSC01033-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"DSC01033\" data-attachment-id=\"656902\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054444/DSC01033.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/dsc01033-3/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054444/DSC01033-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eWe’ve got a full deep-dive history lesson on the M3 GTR hitting Speedhunters very soon, but it’s safe to say the now V8-powered M3 GTR dominated. Over the 10 races in 2001, it competed, it finished either first or third in seven of them. Naturally, that led to some unhappy rivals, so, for the 2002 season, the number of cars required for homologation rose from 10 up to 100, meaning the M3 GTR would be withdrawn from racing… within the US at least.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054236/DSC01174.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054236/DSC01174-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"DSC01174\" data-attachment-id=\"656875\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054236/DSC01174.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/dsc01174/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054236/DSC01174-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054213/DSC01192-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"DSC01192\" data-attachment-id=\"656870\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054213/DSC01192.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/dsc01192-2/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054213/DSC01192-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054218/DSC01187-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"DSC01187\" data-attachment-id=\"656871\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054218/DSC01187.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/dsc01187-2/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054218/DSC01187-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp\u003eDespite its relatively short racing career in the US, the M3 GTR left a huge impression globally and is still regularly celebrated over 20 years later. Even on \u003ca href=\"https://www.bmw-m.com/en/topics/magazine-article-pool/bmw-m3-gtr-strassenversion.html\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eBMW’s website dedicated to this iconic racer\u003c/a\u003e, its (later) appearance within \u003cem\u003eNeed for Speed\u003c/em\u003e is acknowledged as part of its continued acclaim. And that got us all thinking…\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054107/DSC01282.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054107/DSC01282-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"DSC01282\" data-attachment-id=\"656853\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054107/DSC01282.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/dsc01282-3/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054107/DSC01282-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eWith 2024 being the 30th anniversary of \u003cem\u003eNeed for Speed\u003c/em\u003e – and the latest \u003cem\u003eVolume 9\u003c/em\u003e update adopting a \u003cem\u003eMost Wanted-\u003c/em\u003estyle game mode – isn’t it about time we made the most iconic \u003cem\u003eNFS\u003c/em\u003e car an actual reality?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052718/2018-SH_NFS-Most-Wanted-M3-SEMA_Trevor-Ryan-100_51631-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"2018-SH_NFS-Most-Wanted-M3-SEMA_Trevor-Ryan-100_51631\" data-attachment-id=\"656772\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052718/2018-SH_NFS-Most-Wanted-M3-SEMA_Trevor-Ryan-100_51631.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/2018-sh_nfs-most-wanted-m3-sema_trevor-ryan-100_51631-2/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052718/2018-SH_NFS-Most-Wanted-M3-SEMA_Trevor-Ryan-100_51631-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21055730/2018-SH_NFS-Most-Wanted-M3-SEMA_Trevor-Ryan-007_5166-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"2018-SH_NFS-Most-Wanted-M3-SEMA_Trevor-Ryan-007_5166\" data-attachment-id=\"656933\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21055730/2018-SH_NFS-Most-Wanted-M3-SEMA_Trevor-Ryan-007_5166.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/2018-sh_nfs-most-wanted-m3-sema_trevor-ryan-007_5166-4/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21055730/2018-SH_NFS-Most-Wanted-M3-SEMA_Trevor-Ryan-007_5166-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/26160014/HAZ00349-Edit-2.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/26160014/HAZ00349-Edit-2-680x850.jpg\" alt=\"HAZ00349-Edit-2\" data-attachment-id=\"657136\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/26160014/HAZ00349-Edit-2.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/haz00349-edit-2-2/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/26160014/HAZ00349-Edit-2-1200x1500.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eNow, over the years, we’ve seen many awesome M3 GTR tribute builds from all around the world, so this particular one needed to be a little bit different. It couldn’t just look like an M3 GTR… it actually had to be one. And that’s no easy task given the limited numbers that existed back in 2001, let alone 23 years later.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054304/DSC01159.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054304/DSC01159-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"DSC01159\" data-attachment-id=\"656881\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054304/DSC01159.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/dsc01159/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054304/DSC01159-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eThankfully, our good friends over at BMW had a little ace up their sleeve…\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052838/P0006692.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052838/P0006692-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"P0006692\" data-attachment-id=\"656797\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052838/P0006692.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/p0006692/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052838/P0006692-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054535/DSC00968-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"DSC00968\" data-attachment-id=\"656915\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054535/DSC00968.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/dsc00968-2/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054535/DSC00968-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054543/DSC00959-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"DSC00959\" data-attachment-id=\"656917\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054543/DSC00959.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/dsc00959/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054543/DSC00959-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp\u003eWhat you’re looking at here is the #42 Team BMW Motorsport E46 M3 GTR as raced by Jörg Müller and J.J. Lehto back in 2001. The very car that actually won the ALMS GT Series that season with Müller taking the drivers’ championship and BMW Motorsport first in the team standings.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054121/DSC01271.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054121/DSC01271-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"DSC01271\" data-attachment-id=\"656857\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054121/DSC01271.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/dsc01271-3/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054121/DSC01271-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eA car already steeped in history, ready to make a little bit more in 2024. But before you start twitching with outrage over legacy and heritage, don’t worry; its original identity (in paint) still lives underneath – something you can see when peering closely at the new livery.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21053917/DSC01494-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"DSC01494\" data-attachment-id=\"656823\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21053917/DSC01494.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/dsc01494-3/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21053917/DSC01494-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21053906/DSC01502-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"DSC01502\" data-attachment-id=\"656820\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21053906/DSC01502.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/dsc01502-3/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21053906/DSC01502-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054036/DSC01321.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054036/DSC01321-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"DSC01321\" data-attachment-id=\"656844\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054036/DSC01321.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/dsc01321/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054036/DSC01321-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eWhy this particular M3 GTR? Well, this is the actual M3 GTR that would’ve inspired the artwork for \u003cem\u003eMost Wanted\u003c/em\u003e back in 2005. When BMW withdrew from the ALMS series, the M3 GTR continued racing in Europe up to 2005, but these particular cars – although P60 powered – featured revisions to the bodywork, aero and wheels.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052752/32h4uyd6l2db1.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052752/32h4uyd6l2db1-680x962.jpg\" alt=\"32h4uyd6l2db1\" data-attachment-id=\"656782\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052752/32h4uyd6l2db1.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/32h4uyd6l2db1/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052752/32h4uyd6l2db1-1200x1699.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eExtra fun fact: In the \u003cem\u003eMost Wanted\u003c/em\u003e box art, the M3 GTR sits on ADR M Sport wheels rather than the BBS RE594 wheels fitted to the race car. However, in the actual game, it’s back on the BBS race wheels.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21053921/DSC01492-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"DSC01492\" data-attachment-id=\"656824\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21053921/DSC01492.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/dsc01492-4/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21053921/DSC01492-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21053836/DSC01531-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"DSC01531\" data-attachment-id=\"656812\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21053836/DSC01531.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/dsc01531-4/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21053836/DSC01531-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21053952/DSC01358-Enhanced-NR.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21053952/DSC01358-Enhanced-NR-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"DSC01358-Enhanced-NR\" data-attachment-id=\"656832\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21053952/DSC01358-Enhanced-NR.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/dsc01358-enhanced-nr/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21053952/DSC01358-Enhanced-NR-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21053859/DSC01513-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"DSC01513\" data-attachment-id=\"656818\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21053859/DSC01513.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/dsc01513-4/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21053859/DSC01513-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054130/DSC01257-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"DSC01257\" data-attachment-id=\"656859\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054130/DSC01257.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/dsc01257-2/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054130/DSC01257-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp\u003eAll of this couldn’t have been possible without the support from BMW and BMW Group Classic. Asking to transform such an iconic race car – even with just vinyl – seemed like the kind of request that should’ve been met with shouting and despair. But BMW accepted and embraced\u003cem\u003e Need for Speed\u003c/em\u003e as part of the M3 GTR’s legacy and was honoured to wheel out the #42 car from storage for its makeover.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052820/nfsub-vol09-prepareforlockdown-01-lockups-3840x2160-logo.jpg.adapt_.1920w.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052820/nfsub-vol09-prepareforlockdown-01-lockups-3840x2160-logo.jpg.adapt_.1920w-680x382.jpg\" alt=\"nfsub-vol09-prepareforlockdown-01-lockups-3840x2160-logo.jpg.adapt.1920w\" data-attachment-id=\"656792\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052820/nfsub-vol09-prepareforlockdown-01-lockups-3840x2160-logo.jpg.adapt_.1920w.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/nfsub-vol09-prepareforlockdown-01-lockups-3840x2160-logo-jpg-adapt-1920w/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052820/nfsub-vol09-prepareforlockdown-01-lockups-3840x2160-logo.jpg.adapt_.1920w-1200x675.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052814/nfsub-vol09-prepareforlockdown-03-motorbikes-3840x2160-logo.jpg.adapt_.1920w-680x382.jpg\" alt=\"nfsub-vol09-prepareforlockdown-03-motorbikes-3840x2160-logo.jpg.adapt.1920w\" data-attachment-id=\"656790\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052814/nfsub-vol09-prepareforlockdown-03-motorbikes-3840x2160-logo.jpg.adapt_.1920w.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/nfsub-vol09-prepareforlockdown-03-motorbikes-3840x2160-logo-jpg-adapt-1920w/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052814/nfsub-vol09-prepareforlockdown-03-motorbikes-3840x2160-logo.jpg.adapt_.1920w-1200x675.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052830/NFSUB_Vol09_Content_02_30thAnniversary_1920x1080_nologo-680x382.jpg\" alt=\"NFSUB_Vol09_Content_02_30thAnniversary_1920x1080_nologo\" data-attachment-id=\"656795\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052830/NFSUB_Vol09_Content_02_30thAnniversary_1920x1080_nologo.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/nfsub_vol09_content_02_30thanniversary_1920x1080_nologo/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052830/NFSUB_Vol09_Content_02_30thAnniversary_1920x1080_nologo-1200x675.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp\u003eWhy unveil it now? Apart from being the 30th anniversary of \u003cem\u003eNeed for Speed,\u003c/em\u003e today also marks the launch of \u003cem\u003eUnbound: Volume 9\u003c/em\u003e – nicknamed \u003cem\u003eLockdown\u003c/em\u003e – which draws inspiration from \u003cem\u003eMost Wanted\u003c/em\u003e and even features the Custom M3 GTR ’05 along with 14 other iconic cars inspired by \u003cem\u003eMost Wanted’\u003c/em\u003es Blacklist.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052755/nfsub-vol09-premiumsp-04-graffitidrivingeffects-3840x2160-logo.jpg.adapt_.1456w.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052755/nfsub-vol09-premiumsp-04-graffitidrivingeffects-3840x2160-logo.jpg.adapt_.1456w-680x382.jpg\" alt=\"nfsub-vol09-premiumsp-04-graffitidrivingeffects-3840x2160-logo.jpg.adapt.1456w\" data-attachment-id=\"656783\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052755/nfsub-vol09-premiumsp-04-graffitidrivingeffects-3840x2160-logo.jpg.adapt_.1456w.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/nfsub-vol09-premiumsp-04-graffitidrivingeffects-3840x2160-logo-jpg-adapt-1456w/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21052755/nfsub-vol09-premiumsp-04-graffitidrivingeffects-3840x2160-logo.jpg.adapt_.1456w-1200x675.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eYou can see the full breakdown of this mega update by \u003ca href=\"https://www.ea.com/en-gb/games/need-for-speed/need-for-speed-unbound/news/vol9-lockdown-update\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eclicking this link\u003c/a\u003e, but there’s also one final cherry on the cake we need to tell you about…\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054010/DSC01341.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054010/DSC01341-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"DSC01341\" data-attachment-id=\"656837\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054010/DSC01341.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/dsc01341/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054010/DSC01341-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054532/DSC00977-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"DSC00977\" data-attachment-id=\"656914\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054532/DSC00977.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/dsc00977-2/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054532/DSC00977-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054551/DSC00953-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"DSC00953\" data-attachment-id=\"656919\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054551/DSC00953.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/dsc00953-3/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21054551/DSC00953-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp\u003eThis is a real M3 GTR, but what’s the point in doing all of this if it’s only to end up being pushed back into storage again? Well, from today until early January 2025, this very car will be on display in all its \u003cem\u003eNeed for Speed\u003c/em\u003e glory at the \u003ca href=\"https://www.bmw-welt.com/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eBMW Welt in Munich, Germany\u003c/a\u003e. For the first time ever, you can live out that 2005 nostalgia in real life.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21053755/DSC01592-copy.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21053755/DSC01592-copy-680x452.jpg\" alt=\"DSC01592 copy\" data-attachment-id=\"656802\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21053755/DSC01592-copy.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/11/30-years-nfs-the-wanted-m3-gtr-now-real-life-bmw-race-car/dsc01592-copy/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/21053755/DSC01592-copy-1200x799.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eIt’s a properly special thing, and it’s been hugely exciting to see it come together just in time for the \u003cem\u003eVolume 9\u003c/em\u003e launch. Let us know what you think about the BMW M3 GTR and the \u003cem\u003eLockdown\u003c/em\u003e update in the comments below.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Speedhunters\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr/\u003e\nInstagram: \u003ca href=\"http://instagram.com/thespeedhunters\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ethespeedhunters\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
